text:
On tap at Hashigo Zake

- Aroma: molasses (black strap)  strong coffee;

- Appearance: pretty, nearly black but clear, minimal head and lacing;

- Taste: Sweetish, hint of astringent sourness, and coffee bitter, dried fruit is not very distinguishable, might be a prune or black currant;

- Palate: medium to full bodied, possibly oily or creamy texture, carbonation is sprightly, astringent (mildly so) finish, and longish;
 
- Overall: Nice pull but not complicated. Not crazy about this. Should try it later
